title: Timothy Findley - (7 books)
description:
Timothy Findley Canadian author known for his intelligent writing and storytelling. His subject matter is often the lives of troubled individuals.

Poor health caused Findley to abandon formal education after the ninth grade. At age 17 he began a 15-year acting career that led to roles in several television dramas and Shakespeare productions; a protégé of British actor Alec Guinness, he appeared on the English and American stage. He also began writing short stories during the 1950s
